                                <p>
                                Greetings Delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>Welcome to the 10th Session of the Doon School Model United Nations.</p>
                                <p>My name is Tushaar Sharma and I’m going to be your chairperson of the Security Council, 2016. I felt that at this year’s Security Council we must discuss the most pressing issues that seem to serve as a threat to world peace and security.</p>
                                <p>My MUN’ing career so to speak began in grade 9 where I took part in our very own DSMUN in the capacity of an official at the very same committee I’ll be chairing this year- the Security Council! At my second DSMUN in 2014 I was a delegate in UNSC too! From then I have taken part in various regional and international MUN’s such as HMUN China, MCGSMUN and our very own DSMUN for the past two years, once in the capacity of delegate in the Security Council, and last year as a Chairperson of the JCC Chinese Cabinet. Apart from being an avid MUN’er, my interests range from football and music to wildlife conservation and writing.</p>
                                <p>I’m incredibly eager to see how you delegates use your knowledge of the current geopolitical scenario to resolve conflicts that may have a long-lasting effect. I can assure you that this year’s Security Council at DSMUN 2016 is going to be an experience that all you delegates will remember for a very long time. This year’s volatile and controversy prone agendas stand as:</p>
                                <p><ul><li><b>Conflict in the South China Sea Area</b></li>
                                <li><b>South Korea-North Korea Dispute</b></li></ul></p>
                                <p>I look forward to seeing you all at The Doon School in August.</p>
